# 🔥 🎯 AWS Load Balancer Error Scenarios (Cheat Sheet)

---

# 🔹 🟢 1. 502 Bad Gateway

## 🧠 Meaning

> LB reached backend, but backend gave **invalid response**

---

## 🔹 Common Causes

* Application crash / exception
* Timeout from backend
* Wrong port / protocol mismatch
* Connection reset

---

## 🔹 What to check

* Application logs
* Target group health
* Port/protocol config

---

## 🔹 One-liner

> **502 = backend is broken**

---

---

# 🔹 🔵 2. 503 Service Unavailable

## 🧠 Meaning

> LB has **no healthy backend**

---

## 🔹 Common Causes

* Health check failing
* No instances registered
* App not running
* Security group blocking

---

## 🔹 What to check

* Target group health
* Health check config
* Instance status

---

## 🔹 One-liner

> **503 = no backend available**

---

---

# 🔹 🟣 3. 504 Gateway Timeout (VERY IMPORTANT)

## 🧠 Meaning

> LB reached backend, but **backend did not respond in time**

---

## 🔹 Common Causes

* Slow application
* DB/API latency
* Long-running requests
* Network delay

---

## 🔹 What to check

* Application response time
* DB performance
* External API calls

---

## 🔹 One-liner

> **504 = backend too slow**

---

---

# 🔹 🟡 4. Traffic reaching LB but NOT EC2

## 🧠 Meaning

> LB is fine, but traffic not forwarded to instances

---

## 🔹 Common Causes

* Target group misconfigured
* Health checks failing
* Security group blocking
* Wrong port

---

## 🔹 What to check

* Target group
* Health check
* Security group

---

---

# 🔹 🔴 5. One instance overloaded, others idle

## 🧠 Meaning

> Load not distributed properly

---

## 🔹 Common Causes

* Sticky sessions enabled
* Health check issue
* Instance imbalance

---

---

# 🔹 ⚫ 6. Health check failing

## 🧠 Meaning

> LB thinks instances are unhealthy

---

## 🔹 Common Causes

* Wrong path (`/health`)
* Wrong port
* Timeout too low
* App slow

---

---

# 🔥 🎯 FINAL SUMMARY (MUST MEMORIZE)

| Error | Meaning       |
| ----- | ------------- |
| 502   | Backend error |
| 503   | No backend    |
| 504   | Backend slow  |

